Description: Casa Sandoval is a retirement community based in California provides elders with a game room, arts and crafts, and a theatre room.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Casa Sandoval is a full-service retirement community located in the heart of the Bay Area in Alameda County, California. Boasting over 200 studio sized to two bedroom apartments and five levels of care, Casa Sandoval promotes an active and healthy lifestyle for its resident guests. Residents of Casa Sandoval are invited to enjoy the many amenities available on-site including a fully furnished game room, plenty of arts and crafts, an expansive library with complementary computer access, and a comfortable theater room. As well, Casa Sandoval delights tenants and visitors alike with luxuries that include a billiards lounge and an old-fashioned ice cream parlor. Casa Sandoval also offers complementary cable service to residents. More than just fun and games, however, Casa Sandoval caters to active retirees with a well-equipped exercise facility, laundry service, weekly housekeeping and covered parking–all within a neatly manicured and gated community. With meals designed and prepared by an executive chef, the dining room at Casa Sandoval is a popular meeting spot for residents who enjoy the company as much as the food. Casa Sandoval is centrally located with easy access to highways 92 and 101. Located in the Hayward community, Casa Sandoval is convenient to a number of attractions and activities of interest to active seniors. Within walking distance is the Hayward Senior Center which is open to everyone age 60 and up. The center hosts many events throughout the year, educational seminars, and schedules day trips and tours of the local area. Just a short trip away, Casa Sandoval residents may enjoy a walk in the tranquil Japanese Gardens. These 3 acres of delicately arranged Oriental beauty house a large koi pond and traditional Japanese tea house. The nearby Sulfur Creek Nature Center provides Casa Sandoval residents the opportunity to get up-close and personal with many species of animals, and also offers volunteer opportunities and nature study classes. The Douglas Morrison Theater is also a short trip from Casa Sandoval and features live theatrical performances throughout the year. The Vision and Values of Casa Sandoval At Casa Sandoval, residents are the top priority. Management and ownership strive only to employ caregivers who have demonstrated a passion and devotion to serving others. One aspect that makes Casa Sandoval function so well is the solidarity among all levels of staff and their commitment to ensure that each resident is supported and respected throughout their stay. Through instilling high corporate standards, addressing client needs, and maintaining a quality and caring staff, Casa Sandoval has earned a reputation for being the best retirement community in Alameda County. Casa Sandoval was voted Best of the Bay for Retirement Community. Casa Sandoval has been successfully allowing retirees to live out their golden years in comfort, style, and class since 1995.  For more information about Casa Sandoval visit casasandoval.com.

There are a growing amount of "widgets" within LifeGoRound that allow you to view your twitter feeds, facebook news/updates and local weather as a looping slideshow. You can add an unlimited amount of RSS feeds (pure photos as well as text and photo feeds) from your favorite sources of content, and we give you a starter selection as we scoured the internet for you: http://lifegoround.com/blog/rss-feeds/ The fun begins when you add friends and groups to LifeGoRound.  To share content with "friends" you simply drag and drop the content onto your "friends" mug shot (profile image:-)  You can also create "Groups" so you can share with more than one friend with a single drag and drop.  The clever "Group" functionality also answers that age-old digital camera issue of how all people snapping photos at an event can easily and simply share the photos with everyone at the event (such as the Thanksgiving family gathering or the kids soccer game).   While LifeGoRound is a stand-alone social media sharing platform, we have also developed the technology to allow a LifeGoRound-enabled device, such as a "Digital Photo Frame" to automatically receive and "stream" the content from your LifeGoRound.  Sharing photos with friends and family has never been easier or more fun.  As soon as they are shared within LifeGoRound, they show up auto-magically on their â€œeMotion Social-Connect Digital Photo Frameâ€, in real-time... LifeGoRound was demonstrated at a high-tech conference by Sheryl Sandberg, Facebook's COO, and hailed a "clever new way to enjoy your Facebook photos."

Description: Cognection offers product comparison and recommendation services for online retailers to provide meaningful consumer experiences.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Cognection has commercialized decades of research in consumer psychology and behavioral economics, similar to Dan Ariely's work in the book Predictably Irrational, to generate a new type of product recommendation that makes the online retail experience meaningful for consumers by ending frustration, and more profitable for retailers.  Our product recommendations combine the most important product attributes with implicit user preference data to enhance the customer experience with easier choice justification.  Our logic reads: "Given what we know about your preferences, here are the best products for you.  Now let's get you there faster and construct product comparisons that make those products even more attractive."  We identify, quantify, and fix human irrationality to nudge consumers to direct customers through the conversion funnel in a manner optimized for better choices that end frustration in e-commerce.

Description: Hilltop Farms has a collection of fascinating birds.Our breeds includes Eiders, ducks,Pheasants, Doves, Quails and many more.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: HillTopFarm is located on top of one of the many beautiful hills in LaFayette, NY, part of the Finger Lakes Region of NY. Both Otisco lake and Skaneateles lake are only minutes away from our farm. LaFayette is known for its apple orchards and October Apple Festival. We are surrounded by many apple farms including our close neighbor Beak & Skiff. At HillTop Farm, we raise a variety of Pheasants, Waterfowl, Peafowl, Pigeons and some Chickens. When available, we sell eggs, chicks, adult birds and breeders. All our bird aviaries and pens have fresh running water with plenty of natural cover to make them feel safe and home. Our ponds are large and deep enough for waterfowl to enjoy diving. All our birds are full-wing and fly around in our aviaries. All birds with possibility of cross breeding are separated into isolated pens during the breeding season. Our birds are very winter hardy. On an average, we receive 160 inches of snow per year and our temperature can go down to -20 during some nights. Yet, we still get 3 to 5 weeks of hot and humid weather during the summer months with temperature close to 100. Our aviaries have shelters for the birds to escape from storms and blizzards. Fresh running water along with aeration keep the ponds open during the winter months. All waterfowl are raised on Mazuri Waterfowl Starter feed for a good and healthy start along with plenty of boiled eggs. Many birds hatch their own young, some by broody chickens and some in our incubator. Regardless of how they are hatched, all young birds are hand raised making them more friendly towards people.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Food and Beverage

Description: WeDebate.it is an online platform that enables individuals to engage in debates with one another.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: WeDebate.It is a website whose name speaks for itself-- we debate everything!  From religion, politics, sports to pop culture, we debate everything in between. Started back in January of 2010 by founder John R. Cushma, the company found itself gaining attention from the cyber world.  Since then, our popularity has grown immensely and have started to attract a new type of user: Politicians.  Recently, several political campaigns have contacted us asking if they can post their issues they are campaigning about on our site to get feedback from both local and national opinions-- and without hesitation we agreed.   To date, our most controversial topic debated was over Google's new advertisement and whether or not it promoted homosexuality-- regardless of how we see, it is how only one of our debaters saw it that made such a huge impact amongst our visitors.    The very best thing about our site is that anyone can debate without registering-- and more often than not, we are seeing people from all over the globe stopping by and letting us know their thoughts on a variety of subjects-- the best part of being American is our freedom of speech and now the entire globe can join in on our liberties as well and give us their feedback!

Using apps developed on Art + Design’s platform, consumers are able to confirm whether or not the artwork or home furnishing item fits into its intended space, the colors are complementary and the lines and shapes are harmonious.
